## Testing plan

Gates that apply this slice (touches Ui, App, Ui.Tests; no Domain/Storage
change, so `constructor-unit-tests` does not apply by glob):
`build`, `unit-tests`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`,
`impl-log-structure`, `state-of-world-structure`.

- `ui-smoke` — the headless host boots with the constructor as the default
  landing page and renders one frame for every page/panel, including the new
  ribbon shell and the constructor page (AC‑D4 landing).
- `ui-tests` — ribbon shows Build/Element/Trace‑View/Experiment/Settings
  populated from the registry (AC‑D1); collapse exposes every command through
  menus with no second wiring site (AC‑D2); selecting an element appends the
  contextual Element tab (AC‑D3); the *Legacy* entry opens the existing
  dockable screen (AC‑D4); the catalogue lists LS/LP/CP/S/Lens/Flat
  Mirror/Curved Mirror/D with no analyzer entry and allows >2 polarizers
  (AC‑F1); the value‑id action opens a dismissible empty modal (AC‑F2).

(Worker: fill in concrete test names and counts as you implement.)

## Risks

High: making the constructor the default landing page (D.6) reroutes the
app's front door through the existing `RootModel`/`RootMsg` (Shell.fs:94/:121)
without breaking the legacy `Page` paths the `ui-smoke`/`ui-tests` gates
already cover — a regression here fails every existing panel test. The
ribbon↔menu single‑source equivalence (AC‑D2) is the constraint‑0.4 proof
point; both projections must read the slice‑005 registry with no second
wiring site. Bilingual layout flex (D.4) must not truncate RU labels.

## Hand-off

Record the `Ribbon.fs` projection API (how ribbon tabs and collapsed menus
derive from the registry), the *Experiment* tab's command slots, and the
value‑id modal entry point, so slice 007 (Part G/H/K) can hang group /
collection / detector commands off the *Experiment* tab and the element
context menu, all from the slice‑005 registry. Confirm the legacy screen
still renders for `ui-smoke`. Carry the `gates:` baseline YAML block forward.
